          {
            "value": "quirks mode",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Quirks_Mode_and_Standards_Mode"
          },
          {
            "value": " and render the page inconsistently."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Missing charset causes garbled or incorrect text for users on non-English pages."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "Missing viewport "
          },
          {
            "value": "meta",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/meta"
          },
          {
            "value": " makes pages render as desktop-sized on mobile screens."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "conceptual_understanding": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "An "
          },
          {
            "value": "HTML",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML"
          },
          {
            "value": " document is like a sealed envelope. The "
          },
          {
            "value": "head",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/head"
          },
          {
            "value": " is the outside of the envelope containing the address, stamp, and sender info that the postal system uses to route and handle it. The "
          },
          {
            "value": "body",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/body"
          },
          {
            "value": " is the letter inside, which is the actual message the recipient reads."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "DOCTYPE",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Doctype"
          },
          {
            "value": " is a handshake between the "
          },
          {
            "value": "HTML",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML"
          },
          {
            "value": " file and the browser. It says: "
          },
          {
            "value": "I",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/i"
          },
          {
            "value": " am a modern HTML5 document, please render me using current standards. Without it the browser defaults to a compatibility mode full of old rendering quirks from the early web era."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": [
          {
            "value": "The "
          },
          {
            "value": "html",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML"
          },
          {
            "value": " "
          },
          {
            "value": "lang",
            "bold": true,
            "highlight": true,
            "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/lang"
          },
          {
            "value": " attribute is like a language tag on a printed book. A human can guess the language by reading a few words, but a screen reader or translation engine needs the tag to know how to process the text correctly from the very first character."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
