      "slug": "doctype-and-html-root",
      "title": "DOCTYPE Declaration and HTML Root",
      "description": "DOCTYPE tells browsers to use standards mode, and the html root element wraps the entire document.",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "The "
            },
            {
              "value": "<!DOCTYPE html>",
              "highlight": true,
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "value": " declaration must be the very first line of every HTML file, before the html tag. It is not an HTML element, it is an instruction to the browser. Without it, browsers switch to "
            },
            {
              "value": "quirks mode",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "value": ", which applies legacy rendering rules from the early 2000s that break modern CSS layouts. The "
            },
            {
              "value": "html",
              "highlight": true
            },
            {
              "value": " element that follows takes a "
            },
            {
              "value": "lang",
              "highlight": true
            },
            {
              "value": " attribute that declares the page language for screen readers and translation tools. Full explanation at "
            },
            {
              "value": "MDN: Quirks Mode",
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Quirks_Mode_and_Standards_Mode"
            },
            {
              "value": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "callout",
          "variant": "warning",
          "title": "Quirks Mode Warning",
          "text": "Quirks mode changes the CSS box model, table layout, and font handling. Pages that accidentally trigger quirks mode look broken in some browsers but not others, making the bug hard to reproduce."
        }
      ],
      "examples": [
        {
          "title": "DOCTYPE Placement, HTML Root, and Lang Attribute",
          "description": "This example shows correct DOCTYPE placement, the lang attribute on the html element, and why the modern short DOCTYPE replaced the verbose HTML4 and XHTML strings. It also shows how to verify which rendering mode the browser is using.",
          "code_snippet": "<!-- CORRECT: DOCTYPE is the absolute first line, nothing before it -->\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <title>Standards Mode</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <p>This page renders in full standards mode.</p>\n</body>\n</html>\n\n\n<!--\n  lang attribute values for common Indian and global languages:\n  lang=\"en\"    English\n  lang=\"hi\"    Hindi\n  lang=\"ta\"    Tamil\n  lang=\"te\"    Telugu\n  lang=\"bn\"    Bengali\n  lang=\"fr\"    French\n  lang=\"ar\"    Arabic (also triggers RTL text direction)\n-->\n<html lang=\"hi\">\n  <!-- Screen readers will pronounce content using Hindi rules -->\n</html>\n\n\n<!--\n  OLD HTML4 DOCTYPE (verbose, no longer needed):\n  <!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01//EN\"\n    \"http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/strict.dtd\">\n\n  OLD XHTML DOCTYPE (also obsolete):\n  <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\"\n    \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\n\n  MODERN HTML5 (all you ever need):\n  <!DOCTYPE html>\n-->\n\n\n<!-- Verify rendering mode in browser console:\n     document.compatMode\n     \"CSS1Compat\"  = standards mode (correct)\n     \"BackCompat\"  = quirks mode (DOCTYPE missing or malformed)\n-->",
          "output": "The correct example renders in full standards mode. Running document.compatMode in DevTools Console returns CSS1Compat confirming standards mode. The lang attribute examples show how a single attribute change switches pronunciation rules for the entire document.",
          "images": null,
          "video_url": null
        }
      ],
      "image_banner_url": null,
      "images": null,
      "video_url": null,
      "when_to_use": null,
      "when_to_avoid": null,
      "what_it_solves": null,
      "conceptual_understanding": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "DOCTYPE",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Doctype"
            },
            {
              "value": " is like selecting the correct operating mode before booting a device. Without it the browser picks any mode it wants, usually the oldest compatible one. "
            },
            {
              "value": "<!DOCTYPE html>",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Doctype"
            },
            {
              "value": " selects the modern HTML5 mode, ensuring all "
            },
            {
              "value": "CSS",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS"
            },
            {
              "value": " and layout rules behave as expected."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "The "
            },
            {
              "value": "lang",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/lang"
            },
            {
              "value": " attribute on "
            },
            {
              "value": "html",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML"
            },
            {
              "value": " is the document-level language declaration. Every element on the page inherits this language unless overridden with its own "
            },
            {
              "value": "lang",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/lang"
            },
            {
              "value": " attribute. This inheritance makes it efficient to declare once at the root rather than on every paragraph."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "common_mistakes": null,
      "bonus_tips": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "To check which rendering mode your page is using, open "
            },
            {
              "value": "DevTools",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn/Common_questions/Tools_and_setup/What_are_browser_developer_tools"
            },
            {
              "value": ", go to the Console tab, and type document.compatMode. CSS1Compat means "
            },
            {
              "value": "standards mode",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Quirks_Mode_and_Standards_Mode"
            },
            {
              "value": " is active. BackCompat means "
            },
            {
              "value": "quirks mode",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Quirks_Mode_and_Standards_Mode"
            },
            {
              "value": " is active, which almost always means "
            },
            {
              "value": "DOCTYPE",
              "bold": true,
              "highlight": true,
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Glossary/Doctype"
            },
            {
              "value": " is missing or there is whitespace before it."
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
