          "title": "Complete Meta Tags and Title Setup for SEO and Social Sharing",
          "description": "This example shows a production-ready set of meta tags covering charset, viewport, title, SEO description, canonical URL, Open Graph, and Twitter Cards. This is the exact meta configuration used on most professional websites and content platforms.",
          "code_snippet": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n\n  <!-- Character encoding: always the very first tag -->\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n\n  <!-- Viewport for responsive design -->\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n\n\n  <!-- TITLE: 50-60 chars recommended.\n       Format: Page Name | Site Name\n       Unique per page, matches the h1 heading closely. -->\n  <title>How to Build a REST API in Node.js | DevDocs</title>\n\n\n  <!-- SEO META -->\n\n  <!-- Description: 150-160 chars, shown as search result snippet -->\n  <meta name=\"description\"\n        content=\"Learn how to build a production-ready REST API using Node.js and Express. Covers routing, middleware, authentication, and deployment.\">\n\n  <!-- Robots: allow indexing and follow links (default behaviour) -->\n  <meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow\">\n\n  <!-- Canonical URL: prevents duplicate content penalty -->\n  <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://devdocs.in/nodejs/rest-api\">\n\n\n  <!-- OPEN GRAPH (Facebook, LinkedIn, WhatsApp previews) -->\n  <meta property=\"og:type\"        content=\"article\">\n  <meta property=\"og:title\"       content=\"How to Build a REST API in Node.js\">\n  <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Step-by-step guide to a production-ready REST API with Node.js and Express.\">\n  <meta property=\"og:url\"         content=\"https://devdocs.in/nodejs/rest-api\">\n  <meta property=\"og:image\"       content=\"https://devdocs.in/images/rest-api-og.jpg\">\n  <meta property=\"og:image:width\"  content=\"1200\">\n  <meta property=\"og:image:height\" content=\"630\">\n  <meta property=\"og:site_name\"   content=\"DevDocs India\">\n  <meta property=\"og:locale\"      content=\"en_IN\">\n\n\n  <!-- TWITTER CARDS -->\n  <meta name=\"twitter:card\"        content=\"summary_large_image\">\n  <meta name=\"twitter:title\"       content=\"How to Build a REST API in Node.js\">\n  <meta name=\"twitter:description\" content=\"Step-by-step guide to a production-ready REST API with Node.js and Express.\">\n  <meta name=\"twitter:image\"       content=\"https://devdocs.in/images/rest-api-twitter.jpg\">\n  <meta name=\"twitter:site\"        content=\"@devdocsin\">\n\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>How to Build a REST API in Node.js</h1>\n</body>\n</html>",
