      "title": "Viewport Configuration and Boilerplate Template",
      "description": "Viewport meta enables responsive layouts, and the boilerplate bundles all required head elements.",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": [
            {
              "value": "Without the viewport meta tag, mobile browsers render pages at a default width of around "
            },
            {
              "value": "980px",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "value": " and scale the entire page down, making text tiny and unreadable. Setting "
            },
            {
              "value": "width=device-width",
              "highlight": true
            },
            {
              "value": " tells the browser to match the actual screen width, which is the fundamental requirement for "
            },
            {
              "value": "CSS media queries",
              "bold": true
            },
            {
              "value": " to work correctly. A boilerplate bundles all required and recommended head elements into one reusable starting template. Reference: "
            },
            {
              "value": "MDN Viewport Meta Tag",
              "link": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Viewport_meta_tag"
            },
            {
              "value": " and "
