      "examples": [
        {
          "title": "Viewport Configuration and Full Annotated Boilerplate",
          "description": "This example first demonstrates viewport behavior differences on mobile screens, then shows a fully annotated production boilerplate with every element labeled as required or recommended. This is the copy-paste starting point for any new HTML page.",
          "code_snippet": "<!-- VIEWPORT DEMO -->\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n\n  <!-- STANDARD: use this on every single page -->\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n\n  <!--\n    WRONG: disabling user zoom is an accessibility violation.\n    Low-vision users rely on pinch-to-zoom to read content.\n    Most modern browsers ignore user-scalable=no by design.\n  -->\n  <!-- <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, user-scalable=no\"> -->\n\n  <title>Viewport Demo</title>\n  <style>\n    /* Media queries only work correctly AFTER viewport meta is set */\n    .card { background:#f1f5f9; padding:1rem; border-radius:8px; margin-bottom:1rem; }\n\n    /* Mobile-first base: single column */\n    .grid { display: grid; gap: 1rem; }\n\n    /* Tablet: 2 columns at 640px and above */\n    @media (min-width: 640px) {\n      .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }\n    }\n\n    /* Desktop: 3 columns at 1024px and above */\n    @media (min-width: 1024px) {\n      .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; }\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"grid\">\n    <div class=\"card\">Card One</div>\n    <div class=\"card\">Card Two</div>\n    <div class=\"card\">Card Three</div>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n\n\n<!-- FULL PRODUCTION BOILERPLATE -->\n<!DOCTYPE html>                                      <!-- REQUIRED -->\n<html lang=\"en\">                                     <!-- REQUIRED -->\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">                             <!-- REQUIRED: first -->\n  <meta name=\"viewport\"\n        content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\"> <!-- REQUIRED -->\n\n  <title>Page Title | Site Name</title>              <!-- REQUIRED -->\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"150-160 char description.\"> <!-- RECOMMENDED -->\n\n  <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://example.com/page\">  <!-- RECOMMENDED -->\n\n  <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Page Title\">    <!-- RECOMMENDED -->\n  <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://example.com/og.jpg\"> <!-- RECOMMENDED -->\n  <meta property=\"og:type\"  content=\"website\">        <!-- RECOMMENDED -->\n\n  <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/svg+xml\" href=\"/favicon.svg\"> <!-- RECOMMENDED -->\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/styles.css\">         <!-- YOUR STYLESHEET -->\n</head>\n<body>\n\n  <a href=\"#main\" style=\"position:absolute;top:-100%;\">  <!-- a11y skip link -->\n    Skip to main content\n  </a>\n\n  <header>\n    <nav aria-label=\"Main navigation\"></nav>\n  </header>\n\n  <main id=\"main\">\n    <h1>Page Heading</h1>\n  </main>\n\n  <footer></footer>\n\n  <script src=\"/app.js\" defer></script>             <!-- YOUR SCRIPT -->\n</body>\n</html>",
          "output": "Viewport demo: on mobile the three cards stack in a single column at full readable width. At 640px they switch to 2 columns. At 1024px they display in 3 columns. Without the viewport meta all three breakpoints fail on mobile and render as a zoomed-out desktop view. The boilerplate renders a skip link (invisible until Tab is pressed), a header, an h1, and a footer.",
